
### **2. `.gitignore`**

Here's a basic `.gitignore` file to exclude unnecessary files and folders from being tracked by Git:

```gitignore
# Node.js dependencies
node_modules/

# Logs
npm-debug.log
yarn-debug.log
yarn-error.log

# OS-specific files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Docker files
*.log
docker-compose.override.yml

# Environment files
.env

# IDE settings (VS Code, JetBrains, etc.)
.vscode/
.idea/

# Docker image files
**/*.tar
